ğŸ“± Offline News Reader â€” PWA

A fast, offline-first news reading web app built using HTML, CSS (Tailwind), JavaScript, Service Workers, and IndexedDB.
The app fetches real headlines when the user is online, caches them locally, and allows full offline reading.

â­ Features
ğŸ”µ 1. Online Mode (Live News)

Detects when the user is connected to the internet.
Fetches fresh news articles from the NewsData.io API.
Saves articles into IndexedDB for offline use.
Marks these new articles as ğŸŸ¢ Fresh.


ğŸ”´ 2. Offline Mode (Cached News)

When WiFi is off, the app:
Does NOT call the API
Instantly loads articles stored in the local database
Previously fetched fresh articles become ğŸŸ¡ Stale (Cached).


âš™ï¸ 3. Service Worker (PWA)

App loads instantly even with 0 internet.
Caches the entire app shell:
HTML
CSS
JS



ğŸ—„ï¸ 4. IndexedDB Storage

Stores:
Article metadata (title, snippet, time cached)
Article content (if available)
Sync batch number (for freshness badges)



ğŸŒ€ 5. Manual Sync Button
User taps Sync, and:
If online â†’ fetch new articles + mark fresh
If offline â†’ show a â€œNo internetâ€ message



