ğŸ“² How It Works (Simple Explanation)
â–¶ï¸ 1. When the user opens the app:
Service Worker loads cached UI instantly.


ğŸŒ 2. If WiFi is ON:

App fetches news from NewsData API
Saves articles into IndexedDB
Marks these as Fresh
Older articles become Stale


âŒ 3. If WiFi is OFF:

No API is called
Cached articles are loaded immediately
The app works perfectly offline


ğŸ§ª Demo Flow (for Teachers)

Open app with WiFi ON â†’ click Sync â†’ Fresh news appear

Turn WiFi OFF â†’ refresh â†’ cached news still load (offline proof)

Turn WiFi ON â†’ click Sync again â†’ newer Fresh news appear

This demonstrates:

Offline-first architecture

Data persistence

Service worker caching

Database usage

Sync lifecycle

ğŸš€ Installation (Developer Setup)
1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/offline-news-reader.git
cd offline-news-reader

2. Install dependencies (for local CORS proxy)
npm install

3. Start local proxy
node proxy.js

Proxy runs at:
http://localhost:3000/news



4. Start Live Server for index.html
Right-click index.html
Select Open with Live Server



